Vintage style illustration of a massive, weathered sailing ship in dry dock undergoing dramatic transformation—one half still showing its original wooden hull with traditional rigging and canvas sails, while the other half reveals a sleek modern steel structure with satellite arrays and digital screens embedded in the hull. Workers on scaffolding bridge both eras, some in period clothing using hand tools, others in contemporary gear with tablets. The harbor behind shows both old clipper ships and modern vessels. Warm sepia tones blend into cool blue-grays where old meets new. Dramatic sunset lighting casts long shadows across the shipyard, emphasizing the monumental scale of the conversion project. Birds circle overhead in a clearing sky.
